    {
      "id": "l5-shopping-theory",
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "Getting around and shopping",
      "body": "# Shopping and directions\n\n**In a shop**\n\n- **Was kostet das?** — How much does that cost?\n- **Ich hätte gern ein Brot.** — I'd like a loaf of bread.\n\n**Asking the way** — start with **Entschuldigung** to be polite:\n\n- **Entschuldigung, wo ist der Bahnhof?** — Excuse me, where is the station?\n\n**Directions**\n\n| German | English |\n|---|---|\n| links | (on the) left |\n| rechts | (on the) right |\n| geradeaus | straight ahead |\n\n## Quick A2 review\n\nYou can now combine what you learned:\n\n- **Perfekt:** *Ich habe Brot gekauft.* — I bought bread.\n- **Modal verb:** *Ich möchte zur Bäckerei gehen.* — I'd like to go to the bakery.\n- **Separable verb:** *Ich kaufe am Morgen ein.* — I go shopping in the morning."
    },
    {
